{
  "document_id": "isa-5",
  "title": "Isaiah 5",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "I will sing for my beloved"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "He dug it and cleared it of stones"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "And now, inhabitants of Jerusalem"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "What more was there to do for my vineyard"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "And now I will tell you"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "I will make it a wasteland;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "For the vineyard of the Lord of hosts"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "Woe to those who join house to house,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "The Lord of hosts has sworn in my hearing:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "For ten acres of vineyard shall yield but one bath,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "Woe to those who rise early in the morning"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "whose feasts consist of lyre and harp,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "Therefore my people go into exile for lack of knowledge;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "Therefore Sheol has enlarged its appetite"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "People are bowed down, everyone is brought low,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "But the Lord of hosts is exalted by justice,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "Then the lambs shall graze as in their pasture;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "Woe to those who drag iniquity along with cords of falsehood,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "who say, “Let him make haste;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "Woe to those who call evil good"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "Woe to those who are wise in their own eyes"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "Woe to those who are heroes in drinking wine"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "who acquit the guilty for a bribe"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "Therefore, as the tongue of fire devours the stubble"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "Therefore the anger of the Lord was kindled against his people,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "He will raise a signal for a nation far away"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "None of them is weary; none stumbles;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "their arrows are sharp;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "Their roaring is like a lion;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-5-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "They will roar over it on that day,"
    }
  ]
}